OASISFormat:        0.4
OCamlVersion:       >= 4.02.1
Name:               nanovg-ocaml
Version:            1.0
Synopsis:           OCaml bindings to NanoVG
Authors:            Paolo Donadeo <p.donadeo@4sigma.it>
Maintainers:        Paolo Donadeo <p.donadeo@4sigma.it>
License:            MIT
BuildTools:         ocamlbuild
Plugins:            META (0.4), DevFiles (0.4)
PreBuildCommand:    ./build_nanovg.sh

Description:
  NanoVG is small antialiased vector graphics rendering library for OpenGL. It
  has lean API modeled after HTML5 canvas API. It is aimed to be a practical and
  fun toolset for building scalable user interfaces and visualizations.
  .
  This library provides an OCaml binding to NanoVG

Library nanovg_ocaml
  Path:           src
  FindlibName:    nanovg-ocaml
  Pack:           false
  Modules:        Nvg,
                  Ffi_bindings,
                  Ffi_generated
  CSources:       ffi_generated_stubs.c
  BuildDepends:   ctypes, ctypes.stubs, threads
  CCOpt:          -I$pkg_ctypes/..
  CCLib:          -lglfw -lGL -lGLU -lm -lGLEW

Executable ffi_stubgen
  MainIs:       ffi_stubgen.ml
  Install:      false
  Build:        false
  Path:         src
  BuildDepends: ctypes.stubs

Executable example_gles3
  MainIs:         example_gles3.ml
  Install:        false
  Build:          true
  CompiledObject: native
  Path:           examples
  CCLib:          -lglfw -lGL -lGLU -lm -lGLEW
  BuildDepends:   ctypes, ctypes.stubs, ctypes.foreign, nanovg-ocaml, threads
